Package com.googlecode.gwt.charts.client.event

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    EventHandler
    Interface for all event handlers.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AnimationFinishEvent
    Fired when transition animation is complete.
    AnimationFinishHandler
    An event handler for AnimationFinishEvent.
    CancelEvent
    Fired when the user clicks the "Cancel" button on the dialog.
    CancelHandler
    An event handler for CancelEvent.
    CollapseEvent
    Fired when allowCollapse is set to true and the user double clicks on a node with children..
    CollapseHandler
    An event handler for CollapseEvent.
    ErrorEvent
    Fired when an error occurs when attempting to render the chart.
    ErrorHandler
    An event handler for ErrorEvent.
    Event
    Common event from where all events descend.
    HandlerRef
    Represents an event handler reference.
    Only useful for removing the handler.
    OkEvent
    Fired when the user clicks the "OK" button on a dialog.
    OkHandler
    An event handler for OkEvent.
    OnMouseOutEvent
    Fired when the user mouses away from a visual entity.
    OnMouseOutHandler
    An event handler for OnMouseOutEvent.
    OnMouseOverEvent
    Fired when the user mouses over a visual entity.
    OnMouseOverHandler
    An event handler for OnMouseOverEvent.
    PageEvent
    Triggered when users click on a page navigation button.
    PageHandler
    An event handler for PageEvent.
    RangeChangeEvent
    Fired when the user changes the range slider.
    RangeChangeHandler
    An event handler for RangeChangeEvent.
    ReadyEvent
    Indicates that the chart is ready for external method calls.
    ReadyHandler
    An event handler for ReadyEvent.
    RegionClickEvent
    Called when a region is clicked.
    RegionClickHandler
    An event handler for RegionClickEvent.
    RollUpEvent
    Fired when the user navigates back up the tree, typically by right-clicking.
    RollUpHandler
    An event handler for RollUpEvent.
    SelectEvent
    Fired when the user clicks a node.
    SelectHandler
    An event handler for SelectEvent.
    SortEvent
    Triggered when users click on a column header, and the sort option is not 'disable'.
    SortHandler
    An event handler for SortEvent.
    StateChangeEvent
    Fired when the user interacts with the control, affecting its state.
    StateChangeHandler
    An event handler for StateChangeEvent.
